narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: If you are at all interested in the major issues confronting American city politics and/or wish to grow as a writer/thinker, this class is for you!

The best thing I got out of this course was working on a very long research paper. Second-best thing was the group of kids--small, fun. A very friendly environment by the end of things. Horan is great; she will call you out on your dumb remarks but recognize your astute observations.

City politics. I would take it if your interested in urban politics and the way america especially these 3 cities has developed.I would take this class if you are willing to participate and do the reading

This class is a thorough look at the political economies of NY, Chicago and LA. Professor Horan is a wonderful professor who puts much thought into class and expects much of her students; in return, students work hard and spend time preparing for seminar each week. As compared with other cultural history-based courses on urban environments at Yale, this class provides refreshing rigor and realism. Take it!!
I truly recommend this course. Although not easy, it will be rewarding in understanding the dynamics of cities.
